Virtualbox install instructions

Sofie Thijs

April, 1st 2021

Introduction

Although the softwares for tutorial4 and 5: Julia, Python, manta, anuran, circos can be installed in Windows, it can be a bit problematic because of the many dependencies so it is easier to install it in a Linux environment. One way to do this is by running a Virtual Box, a computer in your computer, in which you run another operating system, e.g.Linux (Ubuntu 20.04).

After finishing the steps below, you have a Virtual Box with a working installation of:
- Python, Julia, manta, anuran, FLASHWEAVE
- Circos
- RStudio Desktop 1.4.1106 and >R4.0

For who: Windows users.

Estimated time needed for this installation, hands-on: 30 min, downloading time: 1 hour

Lets get started!

Installation of the Virtual Box

  1. Download and install the VirtualBox (VB) version for your machine. For example if you have Windows, click the first option Windows hosts:

  1. Download the 64-bit MDAWO Virtual Drive Image (MDAW.VDI) from google drive. This file is large (14 Gb), so it takes an hour to download completely, make sure you have a stable internet connection. You will need to unzip this file, which you can typically do by double-clicking on it.

  2. Create a new virtual machine:

  • Launch VirtualBox, and create a new machine (press the New button).
  • A new window will show up. Click Next.
  • In this screen type MDAW as the name for the virtual machine. Then select Linux as the Operating System, and Ubuntu (64 bit) as the version. Click Next. If you dont see Ubuntu64 but only Ubuntu32 bit, read further below!
  • Select the amount of RAM (memory). Tip: select 6000 Mb. After selecting the amount of RAM, click Next.
  • Select Use existing hard drive, and click the folder icon next to the selector (it has a green up arrow). In the new window click Add, and locate the virtual hard drive that was downloaded in step 2. Click Select and then click Next.
  • In the new window click Finish.

  1. Double click on the new virtual machine created it will be called MDAW to boot it for the first time. Password is 123

  2. Review any messages that are shown, and select whatever options are best for you.

Finished! You have now a Virtual Box with all the softwares installed for Tutorial 4 and 5. You can run a small test, by launching the terminal, and type conda activate NetworkAnalyses and then manta -i demo -o networktest, it should have generated a test file called networktest.cyjs in the mdaw folder.

Troubleshooting: if you dont see the option Ubuntu 64-bit

  1. Shut down the computer and turn it back on. Repeatedly press esc key at startup.
  2. Press the F10 key for BIOS Setup.
  3. Press the right arrow key to System Configuration, click the checkbox Virtualization Technology , and then press the enter key.
  4. Select Enabled and press the enter key.
  5. Press the F10 key and select Yes and press the enter key to save changes.
  6. Press exit, your computer will restart and then you can try opening the virtual box again, and now the option Ubuntu-64 bit should be visible.
